  "elapsed_s": 2.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I-- Even though I was a nephew and my uncle had a son of two years older than me, but probably, it was considered, at the age of 14, I was safer.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And even if I say so, I wasn't a terribly worried person those days even.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I regularly went to the Gestapo every day and delivered, at lunchtime, the food and left there some food for the evening.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And whilst I was waiting to get the dishes back, I had the opportunity to watch the activities there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "One of the matters which even today is clearly in my mind-- that literally 5 or 7 minutes' walk from our house was a villa which the Gestapo requisitioned, a Jewish villa.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And it was absolutely amazing to see how they set up what they called the Thousand-Year Reich in the spring of 1944, when the whole world knew that the war was not going to last forever, and they were definitely on the losing end of it.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But they literally refurnished, brand newly carpeted and, in every conceivable comfort, prepared this villa for the Gestapo, which of course, all the goods and services were delivered by the local Jewish community-- needless to say, not against payment.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And whenever, these days, I see people overspending on their own houses, I always say that reminds me that they are behaving like the Gestapo, [LAUGHS] that they, regardless of the cost, carry on, which is not really my idea of living.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This is the period immediately after the 19th of March, 1944.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
